body_html: I also encountered this problem these days. At last, I found that it is due to I have not revised the code downloaded from other's github. Then, python will run the *.pyc file by default and my root directory lack the 'pycache' directory, which supposed to contained those *.pyc file. I hope it will help.

body: I also encountered this problem these days. At last, I found that it is due to I have not revised the code downloaded from other's github. Then, python will run the *.pyc file by default and my root directory lack the '__pycache__' directory, which supposed to contained those *.pyc file. I hope it will help.
